title: For Sale:  REMINGTON 870 COMPETITION Model - Hardly shot, great condition!
postcontent:
I never use this gun anymore, so I decided to sell it to get something I can use with my new concealed carry permit. The Remington is in VERY good shape and has hardly been shot, it has been laying around mostly as 12 gauge home protection now. Here is what I know about it:

The Remington 870 Competition Trap was a single shot competition trap shotgun that is equipped with a special gas recoil reduction system. It was basically a hybrid of the 870 and 1100. However, only about 5500 were made between 1981-86. Since over 9,000,000 M870s have been made to date, the Comp Trap is a RARE variant. 

Mint ones can easily sell for over $600, although I've read reports of people picking them up for as low as $300 from unsuspecting sellers. 

That's the basics of it, I'm not "unsuspecting" so do not try to low ball me... I also have a brand new hard case and a near full box of shells to go with it and I will let it go for $450, remember this is one of only 5500 made in the early 80's and is in excellent condition.  I would also consider trading for a Smith & Wesson .380 Bodyguard!
